All Implemented Interfaces:
Editable, Editor, ValueEditor
public final class StringTextEditor
extends TextEditor

This is an editor for string values as text. It has an option to always intern the strings that it passes in or out.

Author:
Dan Bornstein, danfuzz@milk.com

Constructor Detail

StringTextEditor

public StringTextEditor(ValueEditor target)
Construct a StringTextEditor with no length restrictions or preference. If such restrictions are desired, use the setLengthRestrictions() method. If values should be interned, use setIntern().

Parameters:
target - the target for getting and setting
